description:
WHAT: Extract the scattered size checks (bin/nax.js plan-time 80KB check, local-runner.js retry-time compaction) into one module.

API SKETCH:
- measurePrompt(text) -> { bytes, chars }
- budgetForTransport(transport) -> { safeMax, hardMax, label }
- fitPrompt({ text, transport, sections }) -> { text, tier, dropped: [sectionNames] }
  sections is an ordered list of { name, text, tier } so callers declare what is droppable at which tier (prior-round prose drops at tier 1, structured findings survive to tier 2, links never drop).

TIERS: 0 full | 1 drop prior-round prose, keep structured findings JSON | 2 links-only ledger with instruction for agent to read the linked issues itself | 3 throw with byte counts + remediation hints (--no-fetch-results, --pr-limit, --context-file trim).

CONSTRAINTS: Pure functions, no I/O — callers pass sections in. JSDoc types per repo rules, no semicolons. Existing behavior for prompts under budget must be byte-identical (tier 0 is a pass-through).

WHY THIS SHAPE: both transports + retry path + future transports consume the same logic; today the retry path in local-runner.js re-implements compaction differently from plan-time checks, so users see inconsistent results between first submit and retry.
